Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Arab Londoners - Migrants and British identity
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b061017w
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 13 Jul 2015
Being Arab in London: diaspora and difference in the city. Laurie Taylor talks to Ramy M. K. Aly, Assistant Professor of Anthropology at the American University in Cairo, about his seven year study of the everyday experiences of young, British-Arab people and the ways in which London has shaped and changed their ethnic identities. Also, British identity among migrant groups. Dr Saffron Karlsen, Senior Lecturer in Social Research, explores the degree to which ethnic and religious minorities feel themselves to be British. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less